    "what_description": "Specklinia endotrachys is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae, native to Mexico. It is a terrestrial orchid with a sympodial growth habit, producing a short stem with 1-2 linear-elliptic leaves and a single inflorescence bearing 1-2 greenish-yellow flowers with a yellow labellum. The flowers are 3-4 cm long, with a lip that is 3-4 mm long and 6-8 mm wide. The plant grows in humid, shaded areas of cloud forests at elevations of 1,500-2,500 meters above sea level. Its flowers are pollinated by bees, and it is typically found in association with mosses and ferns.",
